What is Hibernate?
* Framework for persisting/saving java objects into database.
* It uses JDBC for all database communications.It handles all low level work regarding the
database.

ORM(Object-To-Relational Mapping):
Mapping java objects on to the database table.

Entity Class:
Java class that is mapped to a database table.

JPA:
JPA annotations are used in mapping java objects to the database tables, columns etc.
Hibernate is the most popular implement of JPA specification and provides some additional annotations. 